Health Map (‚Äúwe‚Äù, ‚Äúour‚Äù, or ‚Äúus‚Äù) values your privacy and is committed to protecting the personal information you share with us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and disclose information when you use the Health Map mobile application (‚ÄúApp‚Äù).

1. Overview
Health Map is a health-focused location-based app that helps users discover nearby healthcare services such as hospitals, clinics, pharmacies, emergency services, and testing centers. We are committed to handling your data in compliance with applicable privacy laws, including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), and other relevant laws.

2. Information We Collect
a. Personal Information (Provided by You)
When you voluntarily provide it, we may collect:

Full name

Email address

Phone number

Feedback, inquiries, or support messages

You may use the app anonymously without submitting any personally identifiable information. However, some features may be limited.

b. Health-related Information (Optional)
If you use features such as symptom checkers, preferred health services, or facility reviews, we may collect:

Symptoms you input

Search terms related to health conditions or facilities

Selected facility preferences or saved locations

This data is used only to personalize your experience and is not used for diagnostic or treatment purposes.

c. Location Data
Real-time GPS data to show nearby healthcare facilities

Approximate location for analytics and public health alerts

Optional location history (if enabled by the user)

Location tracking is strictly permission-based and can be disabled anytime.

d. Device & Usage Data
Collected automatically:

Device model, OS version

App version and usage statistics

IP address

Crash logs and diagnostic data

3. How We Use Your Information
We use the data collected for the following purposes:

To provide accurate, location-based health service mapping

To personalize and improve user experience

To notify you of public health alerts in your area

To send service updates and app notifications (if enabled)

To provide user support and respond to inquiries

For internal analytics to improve app performance and features

To comply with legal or regulatory requirements

4. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR Users)
If you are located in the EU, we process your data based on:

Consent (e.g., for health inputs or location tracking)

Legitimate interest (e.g., app functionality improvements)

Legal obligation (if required to disclose data to authorities)

5. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell or rent your personal data. We only share your data under the following circumstances:

a. Service Providers
We may share anonymized or minimal necessary data with trusted vendors for:

Cloud hosting (e.g., AWS, Google Cloud)

Analytics (e.g., Firebase, Mixpanel)

Customer support

b. Public Health Authorities
In case of a public health emergency or regulatory requirement, we may share anonymized data with relevant authorities.

c. Legal Requirements
We may disclose information if required to:

Comply with the law or legal processes

Protect the safety of any person

Prevent or address fraud or misuse

6. Data Retention
We retain personal data only as long as necessary to:

Provide the requested services

Comply with legal obligations

Resolve disputes and enforce our agreements

When no longer needed, data is securely deleted or anonymized.

7. Security Measures
We implement strict technical and organizational measures to protect your data:

End-to-end encryption for sensitive data

HTTPS for secure communication

Role-based access control

Regular vulnerability assessments

However, no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.

8. Your Rights and Choices
Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the following rights:

Access: Request a copy of your data

Rectification: Correct inaccurate data

Deletion: Request deletion of your personal data

Withdraw Consent: Stop certain data processing (e.g., GPS tracking)

Data Portability: Export your personal data

Opt-out of certain communications or tracking tools

To exercise these rights, contact us at: privacy@healthmap.app

9. Children‚Äôs Privacy
Health Map is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If we become aware that a child has provided personal information, we will delete it immediately.

10. International Data Transfers
If you are accessing our app from outside our country of operation, please be aware that your data may be transferred to and stored in countries with different data protection laws. We ensure any transfers comply with international standards, such as Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) or similar mechanisms.

11. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We use limited tracking tools, including:

Analytics (e.g., Firebase Analytics)

Crash reporting tools (e.g., Sentry)

These tools help improve app performance. No third-party ad cookies are used.

12. Third-party Links
Our app may contain links to external health websites or facilities. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third parties. We recommend reviewing their privacy policies.

13. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally to reflect new features or legal requirements. You will be notified of significant changes via:

In-app notification

Email (if provided)

The updated version will always be available at: www.healthmap.app/privacy

14. Contact Us
If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this policy or your personal data, contact us at:

Health Map Privacy Team
